Add your ActiveRecord models here.

You can create them by being in the application root directory and running, e.g.,

rake generate:model NAME=User

1. Migrations created.
2. Models created.
3. Database created.
4. run export before shotgun:

$ export TWITTER_KEY=<your_twitter_consumer_key>
$ export TWITTER_SECRET=<your_twitter_consumer_secret>

5. callback function (the route the app takes after user authentication) is set in the helper method. Actually set in the request token.

